commitResults.messageBody: Branch code improvements

By instantiating the Command object in Duke, all commands returned by
   parseUserInput method now reads and writes the same EntryLog object.

   The isExit attribute of all Command objects can be used to terminate
   the program.

2. Command Class: Add isExit attribute

   This attribute can be used to terminate the program whenever the
   parseUserInput method returns a ExitCommand object.

3. Add ExitCommand class

   Allows users to exit the program with the /bye command.

   The execute method returns a farewell message.

parseUserInput is not declared as static. Hence, a Parser object has to
be instantiated in the main function so that we can call the
parseUserInput method.

commitResults.messageTitle: 1. ViewCommand Class: modify execute function    The filterCategory method returns EntryLog instead of list of Entry.    An additional method getEntries is called to obtain the list of Entry    for further processing.
commitResults.messageBody:
2. UI Class: add printEntriesToBeViewed, formatViewEntries method
   There is no method in UI that prints the list of relevant entries as
   requested by the user.

   It is not feasible to use current UI methods since they are meant for
   other commands.
   Adding the printEntriesToBeViewed and formatViewEntries methods
   ensure that Entry objects are first formatted into Strings before
   being printed out to the user.

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove Income, Food, and other entry type classes
commitResults.messageBody:
AddCommand: calls Entry constructor instead of the constructor of each entry type

Classes of all entry types extends from Entry class, and constructor for each entry type  calls the superclass constructor without initialising any attribute of its own.

Calling Entry constructor instead of each entry type constructor simplifies code, making it redundant to have separate classes for each entry type.

Remove classes of separate entry types simplify code.
